of the jewels.

135
00:10:34,885 --> 00:10:37,804
- Intriguing.
- And yourself?

136
00:10:37,888 --> 00:10:41,517
If I told you that,
I'm afraid I'd have to kill you.

137
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,810
I'd like to see you try.

138
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:52,569
Monsieur Sauvage,
on behalf of Her Majesty,

139
00:10:52,653 --> 00:10:54,863
may I welcome you
to the Tower.

140
00:10:54,947 --> 00:10:57,407
Merci, monsieur.

141
00:10:57,491 --> 00:10:59,243
So, are you here alone,
Mr English?

142
00:10:59,326 --> 00:11:02,371
That's how I choose
to live my life, Miss Campbell.

143
00:11:02,454 --> 00:11:07,125
Women want safety, security.
I can offer them nothing but danger.

144
00:11:07,209 --> 00:11:10,003
Some women find danger
very attractive.

145
00:11:10,087 --> 00:11:13,131
Women like you,
Miss Campbell?

146
00:11:14,883 --> 00:11:18,011
Women like me
expect men like you...

147
00:11:18,095 --> 00:11:20,264
to find that out
for yourself.

148
00:11:20,347 --> 00:11:23,058
Hmm.

149
00:11:23,141 --> 00:11:25,894
Madame.

150
00:11:25,978 --> 00:11:30,440
Oh, it's for me, actually. Could your
rustle up some of those cheesy niblets?

151
00:11:30,524 --> 00:11:32,901
Now, where were we?

152
00:11:32,985 --> 00:11:35,821
You obviously haven't met
our host, Monsieur Sauvage.

153
00:11:35,904 --> 00:11:37,990
No, thank God.

154
00:11:38,073 --> 00:11:42,619
You know, I think I'd rather have
my bottom impaled on a giant cactus...

155
00:11:42,703 --> 00:11:45,330
than exchange pleasantries
with that jumped-up Frenchman.

156
00:11:45,414 --> 00:11:50,335
As far as I'm concerned, the only thing
the French should host is an invasion.

157
00:11:50,419 --> 00:11:54,423
